<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1879-12-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1879-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="378" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d378">
                    <head>No. 378.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Comly</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Honolulu</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1879-12-22"><hi rend="italic">December</hi> 22, 1879</date>.
                            (Received January 23, 1880.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 86.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that after
                        correspondence between the Hawaiian foreign office and this legation, and no
                        legal impediment being found to exist, the following American schooners have
                        been registered under the Hawaiian flag: C. M. Ward, General Harney, Joseph
                        Woolley.</p>
                    <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JAMES M. COMLY.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>